 {"id":"asupersync-ewm6","title":"[EPIC-TOKIO] Async Process Spawning (tokio-process equivalent)","description":"# Async Process Spawning

## Overview
Async child process management equivalent to tokio::process, enabling non-blocking process spawning, I/O, and wait operations.

## Why This Is Critical
Process spawning is needed for:
- Build tools and task runners
- Shell command execution
- Subprocess management
- Pipeline construction

## Core Types

### Command Builder
```rust
/// Builder for spawning processes.
pub struct Command {
    program: OsString,
    args: Vec<OsString>,
    env: HashMap<OsString, OsString>,
    env_clear: bool,
    current_dir: Option<PathBuf>,
    stdin: StdioConfig,
    stdout: StdioConfig,
    stderr: StdioConfig,
    kill_on_drop: bool,
}

impl Command {
    /// Create a new command for the given program.
    pub fn new(program: impl AsRef<OsStr>) -> Self;

    /// Add an argument.
    pub fn arg(&mut self, arg: impl AsRef<OsStr>) -> &mut Self;

    /// Add multiple arguments.
    pub fn args<I, S>(&mut self, args: I) -> &mut Self
    where
        I: IntoIterator<Item = S>,
        S: AsRef<OsStr>;

    /// Set an environment variable.
    pub fn env(&mut self, key: impl AsRef<OsStr>, val: impl AsRef<OsStr>) -> &mut Self;

    /// Set multiple environment variables.
    pub fn envs<I, K, V>(&mut self, vars: I) -> &mut Self
    where
        I: IntoIterator<Item = (K, V)>,
        K: AsRef<OsStr>,
        V: AsRef<OsStr>;

    /// Remove an environment variable.
    pub fn env_remove(&mut self, key: impl AsRef<OsStr>) -> &mut Self;

    /// Clear the environment.
    pub fn env_clear(&mut self) -> &mut Self;

    /// Set the working directory.
    pub fn current_dir(&mut self, dir: impl AsRef<Path>) -> &mut Self;

    /// Configure stdin.
    pub fn stdin(&mut self, cfg: Stdio) -> &mut Self;

    /// Configure stdout.
    pub fn stdout(&mut self, cfg: Stdio) -> &mut Self;

    /// Configure stderr.
    pub fn stderr(&mut self, cfg: Stdio) -> &mut Self;

    /// Kill the process when the Child is dropped.
    pub fn kill_on_drop(&mut self, kill: bool) -> &mut Self;

    /// Spawn the process.
    pub fn spawn(&mut self) -> Result<Child, ProcessError>;

    /// Spawn and wait for output.
    pub async fn output(&mut self) -> Result<Output, ProcessError>;

    /// Spawn and wait for status.
    pub async fn status(&mut self) -> Result<ExitStatus, ProcessError>;
}
```

### Stdio Configuration
```rust
/// Standard I/O configuration.
pub enum Stdio {
    /// Inherit from parent process.
    Inherit,
    /// Pipe to/from the process.
    Piped,
    /// Discard (redirect to /dev/null).
    Null,
    /// Use a specific file.
    File(File),
}

impl Stdio {
    pub fn inherit() -> Self { Self::Inherit }
    pub fn piped() -> Self { Self::Piped }
    pub fn null() -> Self { Self::Null }
}
```

### Child Process
```rust
/// Handle to a spawned child process.
pub struct Child {
    handle: ChildHandle,
    stdin: Option<ChildStdin>,
    stdout: Option<ChildStdout>,
    stderr: Option<ChildStderr>,
    kill_on_drop: bool,
}

impl Child {
    /// Get the process ID.
    pub fn id(&self) -> Option<u32>;

    /// Take the stdin handle.
    pub fn stdin(&mut self) -> Option<ChildStdin>;

    /// Take the stdout handle.
    pub fn stdout(&mut self) -> Option<ChildStdout>;

    /// Take the stderr handle.
    pub fn stderr(&mut self) -> Option<ChildStderr>;

    /// Wait for the process to exit.
    pub async fn wait(&mut self) -> Result<ExitStatus, ProcessError>;

    /// Wait and collect all output.
    pub async fn wait_with_output(self) -> Result<Output, ProcessError>;

    /// Send a signal to the process.
    pub fn kill(&mut self) -> Result<(), ProcessError>;

    /// Try to wait without blocking.
    pub fn try_wait(&mut self) -> Result<Option<ExitStatus>, ProcessError>;

    /// Start killing the process.
    pub fn start_kill(&mut self) -> Result<(), ProcessError>;
}

impl Drop for Child {
    fn drop(&mut self) {
        if self.kill_on_drop {
            let _ = self.start_kill();
        }
    }
}
```

