### Output and Status
```rust
/// Collected output from a process.
pub struct Output {
    pub status: ExitStatus,
    pub stdout: Vec<u8>,
    pub stderr: Vec<u8>,
}

/// Exit status of a process.
pub struct ExitStatus {
    code: Option<i32>,
    #[cfg(unix)]
    signal: Option<i32>,
}

impl ExitStatus {
    pub fn success(&self) -> bool;
    pub fn code(&self) -> Option<i32>;
    #[cfg(unix)]
    pub fn signal(&self) -> Option<i32>;
}
```

## Cancel-Safety Considerations
- Process spawning itself is synchronous (the syscall)
- `wait()` can be cancelled; process continues running
- Use `kill_on_drop` for automatic cleanup on cancellation
- I/O operations are cancel-safe (partial reads/writes are fine)

## Platform Considerations
- Unix: fork/exec, signals, process groups
- Windows: CreateProcess, job objects

## Testing Strategy
- Basic spawn and wait tests
- I/O piping tests
- Environment variable tests
- Signal/kill tests (Unix)
- Timeout with kill_on_drop tests
- Pipeline construction tests
